Gombe State zonal office of the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) has secured the conviction of one Usman Adamu Shagari on six-count charge for production and sales of adulterated fertilizer in Gombe metropolis and Lariski village in Kirfi local government area of Bauchi State. The conviction was secured by EFCC, in a case brought before Justice Fatima Musa of the Gombe State High Court 13. Shagari was arrested by the EFCC in July 2019, following an intelligence report. Other suspects arrested were Idris Ali, Muhammad Alhassan Alaramma, Dahiru Salisu and Adamu Abdurahman. They were arraigned yesterday on a-10 count charge bordering on the same offence in the same court but they pleaded not guilty. The convicts were charged to Court, for buying the genuine fertilizer from recognised companies like Indorama, Kasco, Tag Agro fertilizer, Albarka ferttizer, Nasara fertilizer, Golden fertilizer and Federal government fertilizer, thereafter, mixed them with sand and sold to farmers at same price with genuine fertilizer. Prosecution counsel, M.D Aliyu prayed the trial Judge to pronounce Shagari guilty as charged on the six-count charges preferred against him. After listening to the pleas, Justice Fatima Musa found Shagari guilty of all the six-count charges and sentenced him to one-year imprisonment with N150,000 option of fine. The Judge also ordered that the fertilizer be destroyed, while other defendants that pleaded not guilty, should be remanded in Correctional facility. The case was adjourned to 14th February, 2020 for bail application.